          </LEXCollocations>
          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-01-26 11:15:02" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(an idiom, literally: to gird up the loins) to cause oneself to be in a state of readiness</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to get ready</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to prepare oneself</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In the context of {S:04900601400010}, however, it may be useful to preserve the extended figure of readiness for warfare beginning with {S:04900601300000} and extending through verse 17.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
